On 5/31/10 10:52 AM, afsungur wrote:
&gt; Hi again,
&gt;
&gt; I want to store seeds in database instead of a file. And in order.xml i will reference a &quot;seeds id&quot; instead of seeds.txt&#39;s path on seedsfile attribute. So, after a bit researching i decided to change CrawlScope class :
&gt;
&gt; Normally CrawlScope class has :
&gt;
&gt; ...
&gt; ...
&gt;
&gt;      public Iterator&lt;UURI&gt;  seedsIterator(Writer ignoredItemWriter) {
&gt;          BufferedReader br;
&gt;          try {
&gt;              br = new BufferedReader(
&gt;                  new InputStreamReader(
&gt;                      new FileInputStream(getSeedfile()),
&gt;                      &quot;UTF-8&quot;));
&gt;          } catch (IOException e) {
&gt;              throw new RuntimeException(e);
&gt;          }
&gt;          return new SeedFileIterator(br,ignoredItemWriter);
&gt;      }
&gt; ...
&gt; ...
&gt;
&gt; I changed this part of code as reading from database.
&gt;
&gt; Is that true, how do you think about this solution?

If it works for you, I see no problems with it.

Again, though, you might find H3 a better base to work on once you&#39;re 
doing significant customization. With regard to seeds, H3 more clearly 
isolates seed management in a &#39;SeedModule&#39;, which announces seeds to the 
rest of the crawler via an event mechanism.

- Gordon @ IA
